sloping relationship between dBs of visual field loss and QALY decrements. QALY 
losses accumulate slowly at first and then increase at an accelerating rate 
following an MD of approximately -10 dBs. This relationship is consistent with 
recent empirical findings reporting minimal QALY losses associated with small 
visual field defects.

