GAPDH, KL, LEPR, PON1, PSEN1, SOD2, and WRN. Top ranked SNP associations in the 
GEE model for age at natural menopause included rs6910534 (p = 0.00003) near 
FOXO3a and rs3751591 (p = 0.00006) in CYP19A1. Results of all longevity 
phenotype-genotype associations for all autosomal SNPs are web posted at 
http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/projects/gap/cgi-bin/study.cgi?id=phs000007 webcite.
CONCLUSION: Longevity and aging traits are associated with SNPs on the 
Affymetrix 100K GeneChip. None of the associations achieved genome-wide 
significance. These data generate hypotheses and serve as a resource for 
replication as more genes and biologic pathways are proposed as contributing to 
longevity and healthy aging.

