Anaesthesia and the preparation and management of elderly patients undergoing 
surgery.

Severn A(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Anaesthesia, Royal Lancaster Infirmary, Lancaster LA1 4RP, UK. 
andrew.severn@mbht.nhs.uk <andrew.severn@mbht.nhs.uk>

With increasing life expectancy, the number of very elderly patients requiring 
surgery and anaesthesia is increasing. Age, co-morbidity and altered 
pharmacokinetics clearly need to be considered in assessment of surgical risk 
but even in the apparently well older person there is a loss of physiological 
reserve that may be overlooked on cursory examination. Cognitive impairment 
